  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Regional QHSE Manager",
  "description": "<ul><li>Consistently work to all Quality, Health, Safety, and Environmental standards applicable to the organisation and assist in the development, implementation, and continuous improvement of such standards across the APAC region.</li></ul><ul><li>Develop, maintain, and continually improve the Integrated Management System to underpin QHSE and operational standards, ensuring alignment with ISO 9001, ISO 14001, ISO 45001, applicable regulatory requirements, and business objectives.</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure compliance with all relevant local, regional, and international regulatory bodies and statutory authorities to maintain operational capability, legal compliance, and efficient business operations.</li></ul><ul><li>Establish, manage, and support QHSE training and development for all staff to ensure awareness, understanding, and effective application of QHSE standards and regulatory requirements.</li></ul><ul><li>Manage all incident, accident, near miss, unsafe act, unsafe condition, and non-conformance reporting, and lead or support investigations, root cause analysis, and corrective and preventative action processes.</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure all required QHSE reporting, including incidents, audits, non-conformances, regulatory matters, and Cost of Poor Quality events, is completed accurately and submitted to Group HQ within agreed timeframes.</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor, audit, analyse, and report on QHSE performance, trends, and key metrics to support informed decision-making and continuous improvement.</li></ul><ul><li>Conduct and manage internal audits, customer audits, vendor audits, external certification audits, and regulatory inspections, ensuring timely closure of NCRs, observations, and improvement actions.</li></ul><ul><li>Record, manage, and track non-conformity reports, opportunities for improvement, and corrective actions to drive measurable improvements in safety, quality, environmental performance, and operational efficiency. </li></ul>",
